29. find the centroid of the infinite region in the second quadrant
    enclosed by the coordinate axes and the curve y = e**x

    -∞ < x <= 0, 0 <=  y <= e**x


    M   = ∫(-∞, 0) ∫(0, e**x) dy dx
        = ∫(-∞, 0) e**x dx
        = lim(b->-∞) e**0 - e**(b)
        = 1

    Mx  = ∫(-∞, 0) ∫(0, e**x) y dy dx
        = ∫(-∞, 0) (y²/2)|(0,e**x) dx
        = 1/2 ∫(-∞, 0) e**2x dx
        = 1/4 lim(b->-∞) e**0 - e**(2b)
        = 1/4

    My  = ∫(-∞, 0) ∫(0, e**x) x dy dx
        = ∫(-∞, 0) (xy)|(0, e**x) dx
        = ∫(-∞, 0) x e**x dx
        = lim(b->-∞) (xe**x - e**x)|(b, 0)
        = (0 - 1 - 0 - 0)
        = -1

    x'  = My/M = -1
    y'  = Mx/M = 1/4

